# Shipwright churn-artifact merge strategy.
# See .shipwright/planning/iterate/2026-05-31-churn-merge-resolver.md (AC-1).
#
# shipwright_events.jsonl is an append-only event log: when origin/main and an
# iterate branch each append events, keep BOTH sides' lines automatically instead
# of forcing a manual conflict resolution. `union` is git's built-in line-union
# merge driver (no per-clone `git config` needed) and is honored by GitHub's
# server-side merge too.
#
# Rollout note: a long-lived branch created BEFORE this commit must merge this
# commit (so .gitattributes is present in its tree) before `union` applies to it.
# The resolver (resolve_churn_conflicts.py) validates the merged log regardless.
shipwright_events.jsonl merge=union
